  dpop_nonce
}

// Semantic direction:
// jwt is a compact, URL-safe token format: base64url(header).base64url(payload).signature.
// jwt_sign computes a signature over header + payload using the jwt_algorithm.
// alg_eddsa uses Ed25519 signatures — the most compact and secure JWT algorithm.
// alg_rs256 and alg_es256 are widely supported but require larger signatures.
// jwt_verify checks the signature and validates registered claims: exp, nbf, iss, aud.
// claim_jti is a unique token ID used for revocation tracking and replay prevention.
// jwt_decode_unverified reads the payload without verifying; only for inspection, never trust.
// jwks_endpoint serves public keys for JWT verification to downstream services.
// kid_header selects which key in the JWKS was used, enabling key rotation without downtime.
// paseto is a modern alternative to JWT that eliminates algorithm confusion vulnerabilities.
// paseto_v4_local uses XChaCha20-Poly1305 for symmetric authenticated encryption.
// paseto_v4_public uses Ed25519 for signing, producing non-malleable tokens.
// paseto_implicit_assertion binds the token to a specific context (e.g. request URL) without including it in the payload.
// api_key_prefix is a human-readable tag (e.g. "nk_live_") that identifies the key type.
// api_key_hash stores the SHA-256 of the secret; the plaintext is only shown once at generation.
// api_key_verify recomputes the hash and compares it in constant time.
// token_blocklist stores revoked jwt_jti values for checking during verification.
// jti_check looks up the jti in token_blocklist before accepting a token.
// sender_constrained binds an access_token to a client's public key via dpop.
// dpop_proof is a short-lived JWT signed by the client's private key, proving possession.
// dpop_nonce prevents replay of dpop_proofs.

// Primitive flow:
// jwt issuance: jwt_sign({sub, iss, aud, exp=now+1h, jti=random}, private_key, alg_eddsa)
//   -> token string
// jwt verification: jwt_verify(token, jwks, expected_aud)
//   -> check exp, nbf, iss, aud -> verify signature against kid-selected public key
//   -> jti_check: is jti in token_blocklist? -> jwt_revoked
// jwt revocation: store_token(jti, exp) -> revoke_token(jti) -> token_blocklist
// paseto: paseto_sign(payload, footer, private_key) -> paseto_token
//   paseto_verify(token, public_key, implicit_assertion) -> payload
// api_key: api_key_generate -> (prefix + random_bytes) -> api_key_hash stored
//   verify: hmac_sha256(secret, identifier) constant-time compare -> api_key_verify
// DPoP: client signs dpop_proof with private key -> attaches to Authorization header
//   server: verify dpop_proof signature + nonce + ath claim matches access_token

// This defines JWT signing and verification, PASETO, API key management,
// token revocation, and DPoP sender-constrained access tokens.
